  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2020-03-19",
    "date": "2020-04-10T19:33:09Z",
    "text": "Creating Capacity for Communities in Need Act\n\nThis bill provides for an exception, during the national emergency relating to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019), to provisions under the Stark law (i.e., the Physician Self-Referral Law) that prohibit physician-owned hospitals from expanding facility capacity.\n\nSpecifically, the bill excludes from such restrictions any increase in operating rooms, procedure rooms, or beds for which a hospital is licensed or begins construction during the period of March 13, 2020, through the last day of the national emergency."
  },
